# Title: Cab File Extraction Via Wusa.EXE From Potentially Suspicious Paths
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2022-08-05
# Level: high
# Description: Detects the execution of the "wusa.exe" (Windows Update Standalone Installer) utility to extract ".cab" files using the "/extract" argument from potentially suspicious paths.
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_wusa_cab_files_extraction_from_susp_paths.yml

CommandLine IN ("*:\\PerfLogs\\*", "*:\\Users\\Public\\*", "*:\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*\\Appdata\\Local\\Temp\\*") CommandLine="*/extract:*" Image="*\\wusa.exe"